## Memory Map

  0x80000         loop 0 (fixed physical address, BSS workaround)
  0x9100          VESA FB info (from MBR)
  0x9A00-0x9A40   loop registry pointers (set by handoff)
  0x9B00-0x9B28   loop scratch (consumer + kbd temps)
  0x100000 (1MB)  kernel
  0x400000 (4MB)  virtqueue
  0x500000 (5MB)  virtio-GPU framebuffer
  0x600000 (6MB)  CPU firmware (ATA loaded)
  0x800000 (8MB)  GPU firmware (ATA loaded)
  0x2800000(40MB) GSP page tables + metadata + queues


## Lessons (DON'T REPEAT)

- DON'T WRITE ASM AFTER THE EQUATION. If you reach for asm, you
  haven't found the right coordinates.
- DON'T ADD BONDS TO THE EQUATION. It stays sealed. Decompose.
- DON'T PUT PCI SCAN IN THE BOOTLOADER. Non-local reads.
- DON'T HARDCODE VESA MODE NUMBERS. Enumerate, check BPP=32.
- DON'T BLOAT GENESIS. New walk → new file in walks/.
- SAVE PIPELINE BEFORE DEBUG PRINTS. port_write clears pipeline.
- DEREF LOADS QWORDS. Write qwords to scratch that gets deref'd.
- LOOP_BACK NEEDS NONZERO PIPELINE. Reload from scratch after δ.
- PORT ADDRESSES DON'T FIT IN U8. Use θ²ρρ (u32) for ports.
- DON'T OVERLAP QWORD SCRATCH. Space 8 bytes apart.
- ASK THE LATTICE FIRST. Width on τ, register on φ — it predicted
  every design decision. When we guessed, we got it wrong.
- CHECK THE LINUX SOURCE. For hardware registers, the kernel is there.
- BUILD INCREMENTALLY. One change, one test. BOTH headless AND GUI.
- COMMENT LIKE A RETARD IS READING. Explain every coordinate, every
  flags byte, every skip offset. The next wit sees this for the first
  time.
- USE HODOS. Bond symbols, not hex. π̄δ is port_write. 0xC1 is noise.
- DON'T PUT X86 ABOVE THE WALKER. Everything above = coordinates only.
- DON'T COPY DATA IN LOOP_READ. Returns a pointer. Zero-copy.
- DON'T USE GLOBAL STASH. Two cores + same address = Pauli violation.
- DRAIN HAS NO π. bind = ∘+∮+δ. Consumer does the read.
- INPUT IS COORDINATES, NOT CHARACTERS. Don't assume keyboard, shell 1.
